name: treatment of scrap printed wiring boards, shredding and separation | used printed wiring boards | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/11378/documentation

The multioutput-process "treatment PWB for further metallugical treatment" delivers the co-products "disposal, treatment of printed wiring boards‚Äù and "electronics scrap, for precious metal recovery, at preparation plant". The allocation is done 100% to the disposal process.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



This dataset represents the treatment of printed wiring boards (PWB) from electric and electronic devices for the recovery of precious metals in a metallurgical process. It includes infrastructure, energy consumption, and an estimation of the efforts for transportation. The process has no emissions to air / water.
